<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>I think it would be useful to be able to get the columns/fields from a Row or Rowset from a Row you could do</p>

<pre class="literal"> 
function getColumns()
{
    return array_keys( $this-&gt;_data )
}
</pre>

<p>From a RowSet you will need to get the first Row (if there is one) then run the same getColumns call.  I perdonally would use this when building a sort form so providing the ability to sort or not sort via one or more columns in the database.</p>

